A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the Georgia Forestry Commission for serving the State of
2 Georgia as an emergency response agency; the Worth County Unit on being named the 2024
3 Unit of the Year for Service; the Fannin/Towns/Union Unit on being named the 2024 Unit
4 of the Year for Community Engagement; Clark Rountree for being named 2024 Wildland
5 Firefighter of the Year; and Kevin Lee for being named 2024 Forester of the Year; and for
6 other purposes.
7 WHEREAS, the Georgia Forestry Commission has worked diligently toward its mission "to
8 provide leadership, service, and education to protect and conserve Georgia's forest resources"
9 and its vision of "healthy and abundant forests that support a robust industry while providing
10 social, environmental, and financial benefits to all of Georgia" since 1921; and
11 WHEREAS, the Georgia Forestry Commission has protected Georgia's forests and citizens
12 from an average of 3,000 wildfires burning 18,500 acres per year and has responded to
13 historic wildfire events, including catastrophic fires in 2007, 2011, 2016, and 2017; and
14 WHEREAS, the Georgia Forestry Commission assists public and private landowners in the
15 established practice of prescribed burning to reduce hazardous fuels, protect communities
