16 from extreme wildfires, minimize the spread of insects and diseases, and improve habitats
17 for threatened and endangered species; and
18 WHEREAS, employees of the Georgia Forestry Commission are trained to meet national
19 standards as Firefighter Type 1 and Firefighter Type 2 or are POST-certified law
20 enforcement officers, undergoing specific and rigorous training and assignments to maintain
21 qualifications to respond to wildfires and all-hazards incidents; and
22 WHEREAS, the Worth County Unit was selected as the Georgia Forestry Commission's
23 2024 Unit of the Year for Service due to its outstanding accomplishments in serving
24 landowners through firebreak plowing, prescribed burn assists, and other services; and
25 WHEREAS, the Fannin/Towns/Union Unit was selected as the Georgia Forestry
26 Commission's 2024 Unit of the Year for Community Engagement due to its exemplary
27 outreach efforts, including Smokey Bear programs, educational programs, and other
28 community initiatives; and
29 WHEREAS, Clark Rountree was selected as the Georgia Forestry Commission's 2024
30 Wildland Firefighter of the Year in recognition of his outstanding accomplishments in all
31 areas of wildfire mitigation and suppression; and
32 WHEREAS, Kevin Lee was selected as the Georgia Forestry Commission's 2024 Forester
33 of the Year in recognition of his outstanding accomplishments in all areas of forest
34 management; and
35 WHEREAS, employees of the Georgia Forestry Commission serve the citizens of the State
36 of Georgia with dedication, heart, and determination, ensuring the safeguarding of
