37 communities as well as the protection and conservation of our forest resources for the next
38 generation.
39 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
40 recognize the Georgia Forestry Commission as an emergency response agency.
41 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body commend the Worth County
42 Unit, the Fannin/Towns/Union Unit, Clark Rountree, and Kevin Lee for their outstanding
43 achievements and recognition as the 2024 Unit of the Year for Service, Unit of the Year for
44 Community Engagement, Wildland Firefighter of the Year, and Forester of the Year.
45 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
46 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to State Forester John
47 Sabo.
